 Given complex numbers are $a+i$, $c+di$, and $e+fi$. We have, $b=1$, $e=-a-c$, sum of the numbers is $-i$.</think>
<answer> \begin{align*} &\,(a+i)+(c+di)+(e+fi)=-i\\ &\,(a+c+e)+(1+d+f)i=0-1i\\ &\,(a+c-e)+(1+d+f)i=-1i\\ \end{align*}
Since $e=-a-c$, $a+c-e=a+c-(-a-c)=2a+2c=0$. Then we have, $1+d+f=-1$. Thus $d+f=-2$. </answer>

